In order to increase the sensitivity of the whole system and guarantee the dependability of signals collected throughout the RFI monitoring procedure, it is necessary to calibrate the RF chain of the system. The system adopts a three-step measurement calibration method when changing the frequency band or antenna polarization each time. The specific steps are as follows [
					5]:



Turn off the noise source for one measurement;



Open the noise source for one measurement;



Connect the antenna to the RF chain for a measurement.

The following parameters of the system can be obtained through measurement and calculation:



